  console.error(`[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${err.stack}`); // Log internally
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({
    error: 'Internal server error',  // Generic message to client
    // NEVER: message: err.message  (leaks internals)
  });
});
```

---

## 🟡 LOW — Express Fingerprinting via `X-Powered-By` Header

Express sends `X-Powered-By: Express` by default, revealing the server technology to attackers and aiding reconnaissance.

**Recommendation:**

```js
app.disable('x-powered-by');
// Or use helmet(), which does this automatically
```

